Here is a list of what this car has:   - 5.7 Liter V-8 Hemi  - Deluxe wheels in near new condition (18")  - 4 great condition Michelin Latitude tires with LOTS of tread life left!  - Newly replaced spare tire  - Both AC and heating work great!  - Climate control heating and cooling with separate controls for driver and passenger  - Rear seating area heating and A/C vents  - Roof rack with cross bars  - High end factory tow package with the optional transmission cooler and upgraded alternator,  Includes trailer wiring and tow/haul button on the dash to reconfigure the drive train for when towing heavy loads.  - Electronically controlled low range for easy switchover  - Leather heated power seats in the front and leather seats in the back (good condition!)  - Rear seat has pull down armrests between the passengers  - Rear seats fold down easily to expand the cargo area.  - Tilt steering wheel with factory Jeep wheel cover (comfy!)  - Regular maintenance including recent fluid changes for transmission, transfer case and both differentials  - No accidents or damage other than some parking lot dings and scratches  What's wrong with it?   - Not much. My mechanic tells me the code says electrical / wiring issue.  Probably the radio!  I do have a Blaupunkt replacement radio which I will include.  It has been a great car!  I have had a number of Grand Cherokees many going to almost 300,000 miles without any issues.  This should continue to give years of great service.

We are selling our gently used 2011 Toyota Sienna Limited AWD Minivan. We purchased it directly from Fitzgerald Toyota in Germantown. It is a darker blue color, close to navy blue and has light grey leather on inside. For the first couple of years, I used it to drive to work during the week and the kids were in it over the weekend. We had an au pair transport the kids in a smaller car during the week. During the the last couple of years, my husband has used it to drop our now 16-year-old daughter and 10-year-old son off at school in the morning and go to work. I've used our other car to pick them up and drive them home.   This Limited edition is the highest model of the Toyota Sienna, providing the most options. It is a 5-door, 7-passenger minivan. There are two captain's chairs in the middle and a full bench seat in the back. The third and fourth passenger doors are powered can be closed either by passengers in the back or by the driver/passenger in the front via a center console. There is also privacy glass and power windows, plus a dual sunroof! The windows in the back have shades the can be manually lifted up or down to provide shade for back-seat passengers, whether it be babies, kids, or teens.   The exterior of the car on the powered trunk lift gate has a rear spoiler, underneath that hides your rear windshield wiper keeping it out-of-sight until needed. The tires have aluminum wheels, and two tires were just replaced about 4 weeks ago, due to us running over nails in a construction site! The MPG is 16 City/ 22 Hwy and All-Wheel Drive with a 6-speed shiftable Automatic Transmission. Range in miles on one tank of gas is 320/440 mi. and the Sienna can hold 20 gallons of gas. The base engine size is 3.5 Liters with 266 horsepower @ 6200 rpm and DOHC (double overhead cams).  In terms of safety, included our minivan has: passenger head whiplash protection system; rear door child safety locks; front and rear parking sensors; rearview camera; turn signal mirrors; daytime running lights; engine immobilizer; dual front-side airbags; stability control; passenger airbag occupant sensing deactivation; rear height adjustable headrests; remote anti-theft alarm system; 2 front headrests; 2 rear headrests; auto delay off headlamps; tire pressure monitoring; traction control; front, side, and third row head airbags; front fog/driving lights; post-collision safety system; child seat anchors; emergency braking; ventilated front disc and solid rear disc brakes.  For In-Car Entertainment, our van has: JBL Premium Brand Stereo System w/ JBL Premium Speakers; Element Antenna; AM/FM Stereo; Speed Sensitive Volume Control; Auxiliary Audio Input and USB w/ External Media Control; Satellite Radio available; 10 total speakers; USB connection  Also included (not including everything): audio, bluetooth calling, and cruise control on steering wheel; front, rear, and third row cupholders; three zone climate control; electrochromatic inside rearview mirror; electric power steering; front and rear reading lights; leather and wood simulated steering wheel and center console; navigation, overhead console with storage; cruise control; cargo area light; keyless ignition; 12V cargo area power outlet; tilt and telescoping steering wheel; universal remote transmitter for garage door; interior air filtration; power mirrors; 4 one-touch power windows; remote keyless power door locks; heated mirrors; and multi-level heated front seats  There is also gray carpet floor mats, 1 pair of infrared headphones, BLU logic handsfree system and the dual screen rear entertainment system. It is one screen that comes down from the ceiling of the van. Your kids can watch one movie, or they can watch two different movies at one time. The rearview mirror shows what direction you are traveling; and the dashboard also displays external temperature, trip computer, tachometer, low fuel warning, and clock. The driver seat is an 8-way power adjustable seat with lumbar support. The passenger seat is a 4-way power adjustable seat. The rear bench seat is foldable down into the bottom of the cargo area. Finally, it has a roof-rack cross bar.  Please only serious buyers. We will only accept cash or Cashier's Check from a local bank. No personal checks.

Performance & mpg The 2013 Toyota Prius C is powered by a similar but smaller hybrid powertrain than its bigger Prius siblings. A 1.5-liter four-cylinder gasoline engine produces 73 horsepower and 82 pound-feet of torque, while a pair of electric motor/generators supplies an additional 60 hp. The gas engine acts as a main propulsion source as well as a generator to charge the nickel-metal hydride batteries. The electric motors also contribute to propulsion and charge the battery pack under deceleration. Combined power output comes to 99 hp and is sent to the front wheels via a continuously variable transmission (CVT).  Of course with any Prius, the most important numbers relate to fuel economy, and the Prius C does not disappoint. EPA-estimated mileage stands at 53 mpg city/46 mpg highway and 50 mpg in combined driving, making it the most economical non-plug-in hybrid on the market.  Safety Standard safety features on all 2013 Toyota Prius C models include stability control, traction control, antilock brakes (front discs, rear drums), hill start assist, front seat side airbags, side curtain airbags, a driver knee airbag and unique front seat cushion airbags that help prevent occupants from sliding under the seatbelts in the event of a collision. In Edmunds brake testing, a Prius C came to a stop from 60 mph in a better-than-average 118 feet.  Driving The Prius liftback has never been described as fun or engaging from behind the wheel, but the 2013 Toyota Prius C manages to liven things up. Its smaller footprint and more advantageous positioning of hybrid components allow for a bit more nimbleness, though it's still a far cry from conventional hatchbacks. Acceleration is comparatively slow, but power is perfectly acceptable for around-town driving and getting up to highway speeds.  As expected, fuel economy is outstanding. Outside of a plug-in hybrid, you're not going to do better than a Prius C. An unfortunate downside to the economy-focused mission, however, is a noticeable degradation in ride quality.   Interior Inside, the Prius C features a sleek, modern design with a mix of the familiar as well as the unconventional. Centrally located gauges are mounted high atop the dashboard, which can be a bit odd at first, but makes for easier reading. This Prius C Three gets you navigation with a 6.1-inch touchscreen, keyless ignition/entry, satellite radio and voice control. Also included is Toyota's Entune smartphone integration system that adds Bing search functions, streaming Internet audio and traffic, sports and stock information with alloy wheels.

This is a great reliable car. Runs great. Great local commuter. It has a couple electrical issues. Ive diagnosed them and its few hundred dollar fix so I've been reluctant to do them. Windows will not roll down(happened all at once) so i use the ac and the sunroof when necessary. All the heat and ac works good.  The alarm I've avoided using because its difficult to turn off once engaged. Basically I don't lock the drivers door or roll down the windows. My diagnosis is that's all tied to the malfunctioning Comfort Control Module under the drivers side seat. For someone that knows older cars this is something fairly simple. Ive bought a new VW and I'm just to busy to deal with my older car.  The car has had thousands of dollars of work and added bluetooth wireless Pioneer stereo w/12 in sub and RF amp and 17 in rims and wheels. Stereo has lots of bass. I can remove the sub and amp if the customer doesn't want it. Ive honestly put well over a thousand dollars in the stereo. the wheels and rims were over 2000 bucks. So its a fun car and I've been attached to it for a long time.  It has a few cosmetic damages but nothing major. A couple scratches on the roof and dent over the right passenger side wheel.  Its a fun first car for someone and still looks good. Has tinted windows, nice wheels, and great stereo.

Great running L-48 Stingray with numbers matching 350 engine and 4 speed manual trans.  Engine appears stock with exception of aluminum Edelbrock intake, water pump, and valve covers. Fresh tune-up and oil change. Mileage reads 34,000, but I suspect its higher than that.  New 2 1/2" mandrel bent exhaust system with headers, with unique center exit stainless steel Magnaflow mufflers. Entire brake system rebuilt with new master cylinder, rear calipers and rotors, and stainless steel hard lines up front.  New Wilwood 6 piston calipers and slotted rotors up front.  Suspension rebuild consists of new SPC adjustable upper control arms and rebuilt factory lower control arms with DelAlum bushings.  New ball joints and wheel bearings. Suspension is Vansteel Advanced Street and Slalom system, with adustable QA1 shocks and composite rear monoleaf spring. The car handles and stops exceptionally well. Tires are 275/40/ZR18 Nitto NT555g2's on Team3/LT-III wheels. Everything listed above has less than 2500 miles on it. Interior is in good shape, and has black leather C6 corvette seats.  Tilt / telescopic steering column and removable rear window.  Original black leather buckets also come with car and are in good condition.  Rear bumper resembles pre '74 Corvette (with custom built aluminum spoiler and underbody diffuser), but the original bumper comes with car, along with original spare, rally wheels, and original suspension components.  Paint is decent, but has a few dings and scratches.  Very fun to drive.

This 1952 GMC Panel was being built by custom car builder Tim Mattson of Mattson's Design. He was known through Southern California for his show winning designs and custom car builds. He would always look for vehicles that were straight and rust free. Here had just begun building this panel in 2017 with the intention of entering it in the Oakland Roadster Show where he had won numerous awards.  Sadly in January of 2019 Tim passed away. I did not know him personally, but had seen his cars and his work. I had the opportunity to purchase this panel from his wife earlier this year with the intention of building it for a client. With the onset of Covid-19 those plans came to a halt.  As you look at the pictures, notice the custom, recessed firewall, and custom inner fenders. Also notice that the rear door handles have been removed and bear claw hinges with electric openers have been installed. Tim had envisioned installing a Chevy big block with a 4L60-E automatic transmission so the recessed firewall and new transmission tunnel. The all body panels have been fitted as well as the doors. Excellent door gaps etc. The doors have been modified for one-piece glass and I have new glass for the front doors and the original glass for the rear doors. There are several boxes of small parts.  The truck is straight enough for Black or any other color for that matter.  Tim had planned on installing a TCI IFS however it was stolen along with the engine, transmission and many boxes of new parts after he passed away. There is no engine, transmission, front suspension, wiring seat, front windshield, gauges or glove box door. Look at the pictures and feel free to ask reasonable questions.   I have been restoring and building antique and vintage cars and trucks professionally for over 40 years and I know that finding a G.M.C like this one that is arrow straight and 99.9% rust free is very difficult to do. There are no shortage of banged up, bondo filled, rust buckets out there for $4,000-$8,000 and up. I am going to offer it for sale, and if you are looking for a worthy project to build for yourself or your business, this would be an excellent choice.   In the event the you do not have the desire, skills or time, and would like to have it completed your way, then we can discuss that too. Anything you can dream up or imagine, I have either done it or can do it. Mild to Wild and anywhere in between. I will be open to discussing it with you. You can email me through Craigslist and provide your name and phone number and we can go from there.  Imagine how it will look with air ride all around and painted your favorite color. Suede anyone? New LT Supercharged Chevy? Straight 292 6 Cylinder? Oldsmobile Rocket?  If your are a capable and sincere person who would like to see a bit of what I am capable of, please visit. www.retrorodshop.com   If no one steps up and acquires it during the month of September, then as I complete other shop commitments I will be taking it apart and building it my way. Yes it may be for sale when I am done, however the price will increase dramatically.  There is an open and clean California Title.  My asking price is $12,000.00  Yes I will consider offers from serious, capable individuals. I may be open to part trades.   If you are reading this then it is still for sale.
